      • COLLECTION_KEY

        static final java.lang.String COLLECTION_KEY
        Used as key name when referenceing structures nested into the lists. E.g. if we have key of type collection, which contains structures, then we reference it like:
        • myList - reference to the collection
        • myList.COLLECTION_KEY - reference to item in the collection
        • myList.COLLECTION_KEY.key - reference to key inside structure in the list
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • getAnnotationValue

        java.lang.String getAnnotationValue(java.lang.String key)
        Convenience method, for clients, which expect the annotation to have just one value.

        If there are multiple values contributed, then error is logged and first value is returned.

        Returns:
        The annotation value or null if none was contributed.
